            <p style="font-family: 'Ubuntu', sans-serif; text-align: center; margin-top:1%">Self-defense is a countermeasure and the use of force to protect yourself against someone who is attacking you or self-defense is the use of physical force to counter an immediate threat of violence. Such force can be either armed or unarmed. It involves various techniques but the first step towards it is Fitness. Self-defense is needed by both the two genders in this time where mob attacks are a common thing. It also helps in cases of gender violence as there are many that go unreported. This is making learning self-defense imperative day by day.</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Ubuntu', sans-serif; text-align: center; margin-top:1%">It is a lot important today because of the increasing crime rate against women in India. This includes rape, sexual assaults, molestation, kidnapping, and murder. The list of gruesome crimes in India are endless and this is towards both the gender. Other brutal crimes such as acid attacks, groping and eve-teasing are captured in the newspapers time and again. In fact, there are many that are not captured as well. This has made learning <b>Self-Defense for Women</b> more important.</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Ubuntu', sans-serif; text-align: center; margin-top:1%">This is highly crucial in danger and intimidating situations to avoid you from being shaken and froze. It gives you confidence one of the biggest advantages and knowledge to back yourself in an unfavorable scenario. The self-defense techniques can help you to avoid someone from overpowering you or harming you in your domestic. A lot of people are unconfident with their abilities to protect themselves.</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Ubuntu', sans-serif; text-align: center; margin-top:1%">Fight-or-flight situation, Taekwondo helps you tackle both. Taekwondo transforms itself through the different stages and helps you interact with like-minded people. This skill can be sharpened with time and practice to become more proficient and unique. With our personal experience, as well as driven by the news, we hear a lot about the negativity in our society, and this can leave people feeling unprotected. As it is not important to fight always, it makes capable a person to defend himself/herself and can escape the criminal activities.</p>
            <p style="font-family: 'Ubuntu', sans-serif; text-align: center; margin-top:1%">Taekwondo is a self defence martial art. It is one of the most systematic and scientific Korean traditional martial arts. Taekwondo is composed of three parts in English spelling, though it is one word in Korean. “Tae” means “foot,” “leg,” or “to step on”; “Kwon” means “fist,” or “fight”; and “Do” means the “way” or “discipline”. The trademark of the sport is its combination of kick movements.</p>
            <br>
            <h3 data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-anchor-placement="top-bottom" style="text-align:center; font-family: 'Rowdies', cursive; background-color: darkcyan; padding: 10px 10px; color: white; border-top-left-radius:25px; border-bottom-right-radius:25px;">Arrangement of Players</h3><!--<img src="images/clip3.gif" style="width:25%"> <img src="images/clip2.gif" style="width:20%">-->
            <p style="font-family: 'Ubuntu', sans-serif; text-align: center; margin-top:1%">In Taekwondo competition, every fighter have to wear taekwondo uniform with a belt of that uniform and fighters compete against other fighters of the same gender. They are also placed into weight categories to ensure that fights are as evenly matched as possible. In junior competitions, there may also be age categories too. Belt colour signifies the grade of the practitioner. The belt system goes from white for beginners through to yellow, green, blue, red and then black for more experienced practitioners. Black belts then receive their ‘dan’ grades as they progress further in their experience and expertise. In a Taekwondo match, each competitor wears several pieces of protective equipment and these are:<br></p>
